<h2 id="materials">Materials &amp; Quality</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What vinyl material do you use?</h3>
<p>We use only <strong>Avery Dennison MPI 1105</strong> and <strong>3M IJ180-CV3</strong> premium cast vinyl — never calendered. Every printed wrap receives <strong>Avery Dennison DOL 1460</strong> UV-protective overlaminate. Cast vinyl is thinner, more conformable to curves and rivets, and rated 5–7 years outdoor. We do not use budget vinyl, ever. See our <a href="/materials/">Materials Guide</a> for detailed specs.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What is the difference between cast and calendered vinyl?</h3>
<p><strong>Cast vinyl</strong> is poured into a mold and slowly cured, producing a thin (2 mil), flexible, dimensionally stable film rated 5–7 years. <strong>Calendered vinyl</strong> is pressed through rollers — it is thicker (3–4 mil), less conformable, and only lasts 2–3 years before shrinking, cracking, and lifting at edges. Calendered vinyl is cheaper, which is why budget shops use it. We exclusively use cast vinyl because it handles Chicago's -20°F to 100°F temperature range without failure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What finishes are available for color change wraps?</h3>
<p>We stock and install 120+ colors and finishes: gloss, matte, satin, metallic, chrome, color-shift/chameleon, carbon fiber, brushed metal, holographic, and textured films from Avery Dennison, 3M, and KPMF. Visit our <a href="/color-change-wraps/">Color Change Wraps</a> page or come to our shop at 4711 N Lamon Ave to view physical samples and see them on actual vehicles.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do you use laminate over the printed vinyl?</h3>
<p>Yes, always. Every printed wrap receives a UV-protective overlaminate (Avery Dennison DOL 1460z) that shields the graphics from UV fading, scratches, road salt, and chemical exposure. This extends the life of printed wraps by 2–3 additional years compared to unlaminated prints. We offer both gloss and matte laminate finishes.</p>
</div>

