<h2 id="warranty">Warranty &amp; Durability</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does a vehicle wrap last?</h3>
<p>Premium cast vinyl (Avery Dennison MPI 1105, 3M IJ180-CV3) is manufacturer-rated for <strong>5–7 years outdoors</strong>. In Chicago's climate with proper care, our wraps regularly last 6–7 years. The overlaminate protects against UV fading, road salt, and chemical exposure. Calendered vinyl from budget shops lasts only 2–3 years — this is why material choice matters.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What warranty do you offer?</h3>
<p>Every installation comes with a <strong>2-year workmanship warranty</strong> covering lifting, peeling, bubbling, and adhesion failure caused by installation. The vinyl manufacturer provides a separate 5–7 year film warranty covering fading, cracking, and material defects. If anything goes wrong with our installation within 2 years, we fix it at no charge. See our <a href="/warranty/">Warranty</a> page for full details.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do wraps void my vehicle manufacturer warranty?</h3>
<p>No. The <strong>Magnuson-Moss Warranty Act</strong> prevents manufacturers from voiding a warranty due to aftermarket modifications unless they can prove the modification caused the defect. We have wrapped thousands of vehicles — including 600+ Rivians and hundreds of Teslas — with zero warranty issues. Vinyl wraps have zero effect on EV battery, charging, range, or electrical systems.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What happens if my wrap gets damaged?</h3>
<p>Minor damage (scratches, small tears) can usually be repaired by replacing the affected panel — you do not need to redo the entire wrap. We keep your design files on record, so we can reprint and install a matching panel. Panel repairs typically cost $200–$600 depending on the area. For fleet clients, we offer maintenance packages that include annual inspections and panel replacements.</p>
</div>

