<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2 id="leased">Leased &amp; Financed Vehicles</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I wrap a leased vehicle?</h3>
<p>Yes. Most leasing companies allow wraps because premium cast vinyl removes cleanly without damaging paint. We wrap hundreds of leased vehicles per year with zero issues at lease return. Check your lease agreement to confirm, but in practice this is standard. When your lease ends, we can remove the wrap professionally for $500–$1,500 and the paint underneath will be in excellent condition.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Do I need to tell the DMV if I wrap my car?</h3>
<p>In Illinois, <strong>no</strong>. You do not need to notify the Secretary of State (Illinois DMV equivalent) about a vinyl wrap. Vehicle wraps are classified as removable aftermarket modifications, not a permanent color change. Your vehicle registration and title remain unchanged. No special permits, city stickers, or DOT filings are required for vinyl vehicle graphics in Illinois.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Does my insurance need to know about my wrap?</h3>
<p>It is a good idea to notify your insurance company and add the wrap's value to your policy. If the vehicle is in an accident, your standard auto insurance may not cover the cost of replacing the wrap unless it is listed as an addition. The cost to add wrap coverage is typically minimal — a few dollars per month. Keep your wrap invoice as documentation of the value.</p>
</div>

